<p>You can use simple preprocessing via regular expressions. For instance, the following function will decode commented JSON in PHP:</p>

<pre><code>function json_decode_commented ($data, $objectsAsArrays = false, $maxDepth = 512, $opts = 0) {
  $data = preg_replace('~
    (" (?:[^"\\\\] | \\\\\\\\ | \\\\")*+ ") | \# [^\v]*+ | // [^\v]*+ | /\* .*? \*/
  ~xs', '$1', $data);

  return json_decode($data, $objectsAsArrays, $maxDepth, $opts);
}
</code></pre>

<p>It supports all PHP-style comments: /*, #, //. String literals are preserved as is.</p>
